article.headline: Southeast Missouri State 81, Tennessee-Martin 79
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- David Johnson scored 20 points and had six steals as Southeast Missouri State beat Tennessee-Martin 81-79 Saturday night in their Ohio Valley Conference opener. Southeast Missouri (2-5, 1-0 OVC) led 38-34 at halftime, but Tennessee-Martin (1-6, 0-1) took a 42-40 lead on two free throws by Zerek Knight with 16:00 left. The Skyhawks upped their lead to 14 on a shot by Gerald Robinson with 11:48 left. The Redhawks came back with a 14-2 run, and took the lead for good on a 3-point shot by Johnson. Brandon Foust had 15 points and six rebounds for Southeast, Marcus Rhodes scored 14 points and had six assists, and Michael Rembert added 12 points. Robinson had 19 points and 11 rebounds to lead Tennessee-Martin, Knight added 15 and McKale Jones had 11 points and eight rebounds.
